Sentencas: The La0.6Sr0.4Co0.8Fe0.2O3-delta(LSCF)-Ce0.8Sm0.2O1.9(SDC) composite cathode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) based on SDC electrolyte, followed by being calcined at 1073 K, 1173 K, 1273 K, 1373 K and 1473 K, was prepared by infiltration of LSCF precursor solution into porous SDC scaffolds.
Titulo: An investigation of oxygen reduction mechanism in nano-sized LSCF-SDC composite cathodes

Sentencas: The average LSCF particle size is about 50 nm, 0.1 mu m, 0.15 mu m,0.2 mu m and 1.2 mu m respectively after being calcined at 1073 K, 1173 K, 1273 K, 1373 K and 1473 K for 4 h.
Titulo: An investigation of oxygen reduction mechanism in nano-sized LSCF-SDC composite cathodes

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction mechanism in the porous LSCF-SDC nano sized composite cathode is studied through a comparison with that in the porous LSCF-SDC micro-size composite cathode.
Titulo: An investigation of oxygen reduction mechanism in nano-sized LSCF-SDC composite cathodes

Sentencas: The oxygen reduction reaction mechanism in the LSCF-SDC composite cathodes is discussed in terms of frequency response, electrode resistance and reaction order at different oxygen partial pressures p(O-2).
Titulo: An investigation of oxygen reduction mechanism in nano-sized LSCF-SDC composite cathodes

Sentencas: Three elementary steps are considered to be involved in the cathode reaction: (i) Dissociation of molecular adsorbed oxygen into atom adsorbed oxygen on cathode surface; (ii) Bulk diffusion of adsorbed of O2- in the bulk LSCF phase; (iii) Oxygen ions transfer at the interface between the cathode and the electrolyte.
Titulo: An investigation of oxygen reduction mechanism in nano-sized LSCF-SDC composite cathodes

Sentencas: For the cathodes sintered at 1073 K and 1173 K, the polar resistance in the medium frequency range was dominant and step (ii) is the rate determining step.
Titulo: An investigation of oxygen reduction mechanism in nano-sized LSCF-SDC composite cathodes

Sentencas: The low frequency arc became obvious in the impedance spectra with increasing the calcination temperature of the LSCF precursors.
Titulo: An investigation of oxygen reduction mechanism in nano-sized LSCF-SDC composite cathodes

Sentencas: The ratio of the polar resistance in the medium frequency range to the total cathode polar resistance decreases with increasing the calcination temperature, from 70.6% at 1073 K to 29.6% at 1473 K, but the ratio of the polar resistance in the low frequency range to the total cathode polar resistance increases with increasing the calcination temperature, from 4.9% at 1073 K to 58% at 1473 K, implying that the cathode process is limited by step (iii) when the cathode calcination temperature is at 1473 K.
